<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657816>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. (A–C) Condylostoma cf. magnum and (D–H) Heterostentor coeruleus from life (D–F) and after protargol impregnation (A–C, G–H). (A) Ventral view, arrows mark the shortened kineties; (B) dorsal view, arrows mark the macronuclear nodules; (C) anterior portion of ventral view, arrow marks the paroral membrane, arrowhead and double-arrowheads point to the distal and proximal ends of adoral zone of membranelles, respectively; (D) a slightly contracted individual; (E) anterior portion, to show the appearance of the membranelles; (F) diagram of movement while attached to the bottom, arrow indicates the caudal region used as attachment area; (G, H) details of pellicle, arrows mark the pigments (cortical granules). Scale bars: 100 Mm (A, B); 30 Mm (C); 80 Mm (D)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4657816/files/figure.png" .

